    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "Momentum Investing",
      "explanation_en": "Momentum investing is a strategy of buying stocks that have been trending upward \u2014 using signals like RSI, MACD crossovers, and price relative to moving averages to identify stocks with building buying pressure. The idea is that stocks already moving up tend to keep moving up in the short term, driven by institutional accumulation and positive sentiment. The screener above is essentially a momentum filter, ranking candidates by how many bullish momentum signals are aligned at once.",
